# Logging / audit trail

Use the shared `logActivity` helper on Prisma `UserActivity`. Do not invent parallel audit tables or raw `prisma.userActivity.create` call sites.

## Layout

| Concern | Path |
|---------|------|
| Write helper (server-only) | `src/features/logging/server.ts` |
| Types / client barrel | `src/features/logging/types`, `index.ts` |
| List action | `src/features/logging/actions/activity-actions.ts` |
| List UI | `hooks/use-activity-list-page` + `components/pages/activity-list-page` |
| Demo route | `/team/activity` |

## Writing

```ts
import { logActivity } from "@/features/logging/server"

await logActivity({
  userId,
  activity: "LOGIN", // Activity enum
  activityData: { /* optional JSON */ },
})
```

- Call from server actions / route handlers only.
- No `authorize` inside `logActivity` — callers already enforce RBAC/auth.
- Existing events: LOGIN / LOGOUT (auth), REGISTER (`createUser`).
- New event types → extend Prisma `enum Activity` + migrate + generate, then pass the new value.

## Reading

```ts
await authorize(Actions.logging.read) // ADMIN only
can(me.role, Actions.logging.read)    // client gate
```

Read-only list: `DynamicTable` + `toActivityTableRow`, no forms/modals/row actions.

## Import hygiene

| Code | From |
|------|------|
| Server writes | `@/features/logging/server` |
| Client types | `@/features/logging` |
| Never | `server.ts` from client |

See `.docs/components/logging.md` for the full human guide.
